{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 REVIEW (G6 — approach soundness, anti-patterns & alternative-selection) on the docs plan \"Docs: private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model\" (the S6/docs companion to the repo-snapshot-isolation work). Grounded live against src/rebar/signing.py:1-56 and the repo-wide absence of any in-toto artifact.\n\nSCOPE NOTE: this is a DOCUMENTATION deliverable (Scope: \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). For G6 the \"mechanism\" is \"author docs covering five named topics into the existing MCP-setup docs,\" which is a mechanically-sound, well-understood change with no real structural design choice — so much of G6 is PASS / not-applicable (no alternatives to manufacture for a forced doc-authoring solution). The one G6-relevant risk is mechanism/fitness CORRECTNESS of the FACTS the docs commit to describe.\n\nAFFIRMATIONS (G6 criteria passed):\n- Fitness-for-purpose: the plan solves the actual named problem (operators/agents need credential guidance + clear failures for the new fetch-from-origin requirement), not a proxy. The \"Why\" ties each doc topic to a concrete operational gap the snapshot model introduces.\n- Mechanism correctness — HMAC trust model: the trust-model facts the plan commits to document are ACCURATE against the code. signing.py:1-33,49-56 confirms HMAC-SHA256, environment-bound symmetric key (REBAR_SIGNING_KEY / per-env .signing-key), key never leaves the environment, key_id fingerprinting — i.e. exactly \"integrity + intra-domain authenticity only; no non-repudiation / public verifiability / transparency.\" Documenting that limit is correct and well-grounded.\n- Mechanism correctness — ref/source + env knobs: the attested(default, pinned SHA, signs)/local(in-place, never signs)/origin-main-default semantics and the REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + disk-cap + EFS/NFS-flock-caveat (xref alto-fruit-punch) all match the sibling plan + alto-fruit-punch's design note; documenting them is sound and the cross-ref is correct.\n- Positive rationale: present — the \"Why\" states why these docs are needed (\"the server must be able to fetch from origin ... Operators and agents need clear guidance and clear failures\"). G6's positive-rationale requirement is satisfied; no rejected-alternatives section required.\n\nFINDING (1):\n\n- [ ] [G6 — mechanism/fitness correctness; documenting an artifact shape the code does NOT produce and the sibling plan has NOT resolved] The plan commits to \"Document ... the in-toto Statement shape\" (## What, HMAC bullet) and AC4 (\"the in-toto Statement shape are documented\"). But (a) there is NO in-toto Statement anywhere in the codebase — the actual signed payload is the rebar-native canonical JSON {v, algorithm, ticket_id, manifest} (signing.py:19-25,~188-201) with head_sha recorded as audit-metadata-ONLY, not an in-toto Statement/predicate envelope; a repo-wide search for \"in-toto\"/\"Statement\"/\"predicate\" finds no such artifact in signing. And (b) the snapshot-isolation plan's verified_at_sha binding — the very content an in-toto-style attestation Statement would carry — is an OPEN, UNRESOLVED design seam flagged by the prior G6/T8/T11 passes on this epic (does the SHA bind into the signed payload or stay audit-only? still undecided). So as written this doc plan risks documenting a format (in-toto Statement) that the implementation does not currently emit and whose final shape is still in dispute — i.e. the docs could describe an artifact that never ships, or ship describing the wrong envelope. Please ground/sequence this: either (i) document the ACTUAL signed-payload shape as it exists ({v, algorithm, ticket_id, manifest} + key_id + audit metadata), naming in-toto only as a conceptual analogy if intended, or (ii) make this AC explicitly DEPEND on the snapshot-isolation signing-seam decision (verified_at_sha binding) landing first, so the documented Statement shape matches what the code actually produces.\n  - location: \"## What\" → HMAC bullet (\"the in-toto Statement shape\"); Acceptance Criteria line 4 (\"the in-toto Statement shape are documented\"); src/rebar/signing.py:1-33,19-25 (actual payload is native, head_sha audit-only, no in-toto envelope); cross-ref the OPEN verified_at_sha binding seam (prior G6/T8/T11 passes on this epic).\n  - suggested_fix: Reword the deliverable to \"document the signed-attestation payload shape AS IMPLEMENTED in signing.py ({v, algorithm, ticket_id, manifest}, key_id fingerprint, head_sha/verified_at_sha audit fields), noting any in-toto Statement as an explicit conceptual analogy not a literal wire format,\" AND add a dependency/sequencing note that the verified_at_sha portion of the documented shape is settled by the snapshot-isolation signing-seam decision — so the docs are written against the resolved shape, not a speculative one.\n\nEverything else in the docs plan's approach (credential requirement, descriptive-error doc, fail-closed-vs-local-still-runs, ref/source semantics, env knobs + flock xref) is sound, fact-accurate against the code, and well-specified for G6."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782522354083565001,"uuid":"c62ce83c-1df1-4c85-918c-f137b54fb16c"}